diff:1620525226:1620439520:=51,59c51%0a%3c #foxbegin 210509-015347-675550#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!How nouns are formed in Mohawk %0a%3c -> - BenP%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c I found some more research as to how nouns are formed in Mohawk. There are essentially three parts to Mohawk: the prefix, stem, and suffix. The prefix contains information about gender number or person, the stem information about what the noun actually is, and the suffix, which is option, information about the place or attributes about the noun. %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210509-015347-675550#%0a---%0a> %0a
